<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the Care Quality Commission</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> 02)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This memorandum has been prepared for the Health Select Committee in advance of the Annual Accountability Hearing for the Care Quality Commission. It covers the following points: </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.63pt; padding-left:5.37pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Strategy implementation </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The role of the Chief Inspectors </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.63pt; padding-left:5.37pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Single Failure Regime </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Putting people at the heart of what we do</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.63pt; padding-left:5.37pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Culture at CQC</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 65.41pt; padding-left:6.59pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">University Hospitals Morecambe Bay NHS Foundation Trust</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Governance structure</span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">CQC is transforming the way it regulates across health and care providers. This is not an incremental set of changes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> everything from our approach to inspection, our use of data, our enforcement and our basic governance is being overhauled. The 'glue' that holds these changes together and makes them coherent is that we will always approach regulation from the perspective of what is right for people who use services </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> we are independent of the system and on the side of the public.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our changes start with our own governance. We have a completely new executive team including three Chief Inspectors and a largely new, unitary Board. Our purpose is now clear: to make sure health and social care services provide people with safe, effective, compassionate, high-quality care; and to encourage care services to improve. We have begun to implement a strategy to 2016, and our recent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">A New Start</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> consultation has been strongly supported by the public, providers and national stakeholders. We are also in the process of setting up a strong user-led scrutiny function, a People's Panel, so that those who use services are able to hold CQC to account for whether we are delivering our purpose.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have started delivering changes on the ground as well. In the acute hospitals sector, we have completed our first four in-depth inspections of trusts (Croydon, Airedale, Taunton and Wolverhampton) and will have completed 18 by Christmas. We are publishing later in October our 'hospital monitoring' list, showing which trusts have the greatest risks to quality on the basis of robust, nationally comparable data. This will strongly inform what, where and when we inspect hospitals and should act as a spur to Trust Boards to challenge the quality of care in their organisations. We have already changed to a more rigorous registration requirement for providers of Learning Disability services, and will be rolling this out across all our sectors. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">On 15 October we set out our early thinking on our priorities for adult social care in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">A Fresh Start for the Regulation and Inspection of Adult Social Care, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">outlining proposals for transforming how we will monitor, inspect and regulate care homes and other adult social care services, with a greater focus on public involvement and improvement. Our next steps will be to discuss and explore these proposals with the public, people who use services and their carers, care providers,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">our staff, and organisations with an interest in our work, ahead of a public consultation in spring 2014.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This is only the beginning of our three year programme of transformation however, and we have set ourselves tough but achievable goals for where we want to be by April 2014:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we will have a new organisational structure in place, with our inspectors specialising within directorates headed by each of the Chief Inspectors</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we will have completed around 35 in-depth acute hospital inspections, with the majority of these receiving an overall rating, as well as ratings of specific services, and against each of our five key questions (whether the provider is safe, effective, caring, responsive to people's needs and well-led)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">we will have completed our first wave of mental health inspections, using our new approach to these services (integrating our regulatory powers and our Mental Health Act role)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">our new inspection programme for out-of-hours primary care will be half-way through, and</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">our new GP and adult social care inspections will have started</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We also made a commitment in our 2013/14 Business Plan to improve our understanding of how well different care services work together by introducing thematic reviews of people’s experiences of care when they move between services. We have set up a Thematic Activity Strategy Board which is overseeing the approach to topic selection, the development of new methods and our thematic work as a whole. Our current thematic work includes themed inspections on dementia, the transition of children with complex health needs from children’s to adult health services, and a thematic probe on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">induction for healthcare and care assistants. Two additional topics, end of life care and emergency mental health care, have been agreed and work on scoping these is underway. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our commitment to the public and providers is to design our new approach with them, and we have a series of events underway to do this. While we are clear that final decisions for how we regulate within the legal framework sit with us, we will be listening, engaging and changing our approach based on what people tell us is needed and will be most useful. We will equally be listening to what people tell us about the care they receive, and that carers and staff have witnessed. As part of our acute inspection programme, it is our intention to reach out to recent whistleblowers</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and a representative sample of people who have raised concerns, to inform what we need to test when on-site. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are pleased that the changes we have started to make have been supported both by the public and our staff. Responses to our recent consultation showed overwhelming support for our new approach, and our recent staff survey showed that 82% of respondents felt that CQC is changing for the better, compared to 52% in 2012. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">These changes have taken place while we continue to deliver on our current inspection programme. As at the first week of October, we have already inspected over 17,000 locations this year against our business plan commitment; this is compared to just under 10,000 undertaken against the business plan programme of scheduled inspection activity this time last year. In </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2012/13</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> we carried out a total of 35,371 inspections, more than twice as many in 2011/12, and met our commitments to inspect every acute hospital and care home</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This breaks down as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">845 inspections of NHS trusts</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">27,678 inspections of adult social care services</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2,434 inspections of independent health care services</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4,161 inspections of dental care services</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">253 inspections of independent ambulances</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We also registered 7,634 providers of primary medical services, including GPs.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Six providers were refused registration: three of these did not appeal; two of these have now closed and the third has now been registered following a change in their ownership. The remaining three did appeal, one was rejected and, the other two are currently in the appeals process. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Over the year we published a total of 910 warning notices in response to unacceptable care we found. This compared with 638 warning notices in 2011/12. We issued 83% of warning notices within 14 days of identifying the need for one, against a business plan target of 90%. A total of 75 providers de-registered due to intervention by CQC, and in six cases we used our enforcement powers to either urgently suspend provider registrations or urgently impose conditions or variation of conditions.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><br /><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Strategy implementation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The strategy sets out a clear purpose and role for CQC. Our purpose is to make sure health and social care services provide people with safe, effective, compassionate, high-quality care and we encourage care services to improve. Our role is to monitor, inspect and regulate services to make sure they meet fundamental standards of quality and safety and we publish what we find, including performance ratings to help people choose care.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">To deliver these, we are making fundamental changes to how we work, including introducing a differentiated approach to regulation, moving away from a ‘one-size-fits-all’ model to a system where </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">standards and regulatory methods are developed appropriately for each sector. Inspections will be more thorough, and a new ratings system for provider organisations will be introduced. Underpinning this approach are five key questions that we will ask about care services: </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Are they safe? </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Are they effective? </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Are they caring? </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Are they responsive to people’s needs? </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Are they well-led? </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">These questions will be supported by new fundamental standards and a new surveillance model.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our new model of assessment and inspection is driven by making sure health and social care services provide people with safe, effective, compassionate, high quality care and supporting quality improvement rather than purely checking whether providers are compliant with regulations.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The new surveillance model is built on a suite of indicators which relate to these five key questions.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The indicators draw on a wide range of data sources, from patients’ experiences, staff feedback as well as core patient data sets such as HES, to provide insight that will help direct our inspections and follow up activities. The indicators will be used to raise questions about the quality of care but will not be used on their own to make final judgements. These judgements will always be based on a combination of what we find at inspection, national surveillance data and local information from the trust and other organisations. This insight will help us to decide what we need to inspect, where and when. This means that we can anticipate, identify and respond more quickly to services that are failing, or at risk of failing.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We will begin to publish the analysis from our newly developed surveillance model from 24</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> October, when we will publish this analysis for acute and specialist trusts.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The publication will include a full definition for each indicator and the methodology for creating a ‘risk banding’ for each trust. The analysis will be accompanied by clear messages about what the analysis is intended to support, and also to explain what the analysis does not do.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">New Government regulations on quality and safety will set the outcomes that providers must deliver in order not to breach the regulations; these regulations will form the basis of fundamental standards of quality and safety.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">CQC guidance about compliance with the regulations will specify what providers need to do to ensure that fundamental standards are being met. The standards and guidance will be co-developed with providers, key stakeholders and people who use services, and will be subject to public consultation. The standards and guidance will be tailored to each sector.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">When we inspect a provider, our starting point will be to look at whether it provides ‘good’ services for people, if it does we will explore whether it provides outstanding care. We will award a rating accordingly and will share what we have seen about good and outstanding care. This will include, for example, meeting NICE Quality Standards and developmental statements, delivering care in accordance with other nationally and internationally recognised guidance and standards, achieving accreditation awards, providing innovative services, being recognised by users and carers as delivering good/outstanding services, or delivering nationally or internationally recognised services. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If a provider is not providing good care we will require it to make improvements. If a provider is in breach of a regulation, and therefore a fundamental standard, we will take appropriate, proportionate action to ensure it complies with regulations up to and including moving directly to prosecution or closing a service down – and awarding a rating to reflect this.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">For the NHS, we will work with Monitor and the NHS Trust Development Authority to implement a single failure regime as appropriate.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Again, the rating awarded will reflect the implementation of the failure regime.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We launched our hospital inspection programme in July 2013, and are currently working on how we will develop and roll out our approach across other sectors, delivered by the Chief Inspector of Adult Social Care and the Chief Inspector of General Practice.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We will publish more information about our intentions in these sectors in autumn 2013, starting with the publication on 15 October of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">A Fresh Start for the Regulation and Inspection of Adult Social Care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The first hospital inspections have used a larger number of inspectors – the teams have been made up of 25-30 people, a mix of inspectors, experts by experience, clinicians (both senior and junior), analysts and programme support.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">These teams have spent 2–3 days in a hospital inspecting a range of areas including medical and surgical wards, A&amp;E and maternity; and talking to a variety of staff, patients and family members in a range of formal interviews, focus groups, open meetings with members of the public, which we have called listening events, and informal discussions with patients on wards and in outpatient clinics. Smaller sub-groups of the team return unannounced after the initial inspection, usually through several visits, to follow up on the issues identified.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Through the first 18 inspections we are testing various different approaches and refining the way we carry out inspections in preparation for the roll-out of the full hospital inspection programme in April 2014, and to inform the development of how we will inspect other types of hospitals in future, including mental health services, as well as considering whether we can apply the principles of what we have developed for hospitals to other sectors.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As we roll out the new approach to hospital inspections we will continue to test, evaluate and refine it. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We will also be developing and testing our approach to how we will award ratings to providers.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Initially, ratings will be given to hospital trusts and we will explore how quickly we can also rate individual services such as critical care or A&amp;E. We will begin to award ratings for adult social care and primary care in line with the roll out of our new regulatory approach in these sectors. The anticipated timescale for these changes can be found appended to this memorandum.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have introduced a more stringent test for providers applying to register with us to provide care, starting with those offering services for people with learning disabilities, and are in the process of determining what checks and assessments should be undertaken for all providers in the future.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are asking all new providers of learning disability services to complete a more detailed statement of purpose which sets out the provider’s public commitment, what services it offers, the quality of care that can be expected and how these services are going to be delivered.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our aim is to provide a rigorous, consistent and proportionate approach to registration in order to prevent poor providers from becoming registered. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are changing the structure of our organisation to support our new approach.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">New Executive Directors of Strategy and Intelligence, and Change, have been appointed, as have three Chief Inspectors – for Hospitals, Adult Social Care and General Practice, and each is making changes to their areas to ensure the organisation is working to support our strategy.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Inspectors will specialise in one area, and will no longer be expected to carry out inspections of all types of providers.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have recently appointed Heads of Hospital Inspections who will lead teams carrying out inspections in hospitals, and in due course we will appoint heads of social care inspection and heads of general practice inspection.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Government has given us additional funding to ensure these changes can be made, whilst inspections carry on as usual through the development, piloting and implementation of this new approach. Our budget for 2013/14 is as follows:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 324pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:42.55pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:262.25pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:85.05pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2013/14</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:77.95pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2012/13</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:262.25pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Recurring budget (including </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Healthwatch</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> England)</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:85.05pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">£160m</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:77.95pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">£153m</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:262.25pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Transformation budget</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:85.05pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">£20m</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:77.95pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-rig